The paper deals with constructions of graphs and association schemes from functions over finite fields, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of bent functions, which are commonly used in coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
